    	</div>

    	<div class="comment_content">
    		<p>While this metallic glass is an interesting, and I&#8217;m sure, useful technology in it&#8217;s own right, at some point one has to wonder if it&#8217;s realistic to use materials like this, and the energy it takes to create and utilize, for such temporary products.</p>
<p>At a time when when energy costs are soaring and resources are dwindling, it just seems crazy to be using technologies like this and HTC&#8217;s MAO coating, on rather mundane products that are typically replaced every 1 to 2 years.</p>
<p>With this much time, energy, resources and attention being invested in the design and manufacturing of&#8230; cell phones, of all things, one might think humanity as a whole has already solved all it&#8217;s problems.  Sadly, this is far from the case.</p>
<p>It just strikes me that priorities are a bit askew.</p>

    	</div>

		
