			        		<a class="avatar" href="http://blogs.forbes.com/people/glennalexander/">
    				    					<img src="http://blogs-images.forbes.com/cache/gravatars/glennalexander_40.jpg" alt="Glenn Alexander" />
    				        		</a>
			
			               	<a class="user_name" href="http://blogs.forbes.com/people/glennalexander/">Glenn Alexander</a>
            
    		



    		
    		    		<span class="timestamp">17 hours ago</span>
    	</div>

    	<div class="comment_content">
    		<p>&#8220;Using stronger materials is encouraging news for any iPhone owner who has exposed their Apple product to pretty much any kind of stress, ever. But while the exterior may be stronger, I have a feeling the electronics will still mysteriously give out as Apple plans to unveil a new model.&#8221;</p>
<p>Frankly, I&#8217;ve had an iPhone from day 1, plus I&#8217;ve purchased every iPhone model released every year afterwards. And after owning 5 iPhones which I use thoroughly every day I cannot at all agree with your remark suggesting iPhone isn&#8217;t resilient and reliable.</p>
<p>Of course I&#8217;ve kept my iPhone inside the usual bumper case to protect it. But over the years my iPhones have fallen onto hard surfaces and have been put through the rigors and stress of any mobile device that&#8217;s carried everywhere and used extensively. During all that time I&#8217;ve never seen a scratch and certainly no breakage, ever!</p>
<p>Maybe I&#8217;m just lucky. But instead, I think I know more about the splendid quality of iPhone than your negative inference in this article.</p>
<p>Also, I don&#8217;t know exactly what you mean when you say, &#8220;I have a feeling the electronics will still mysteriously give out as Apple plans to unveil a new model.&#8221; But again your statement suggests iPhone has less than a generally distinguished reputation for reliability giving product satisfaction and immense enjoyment. Yours is a bias that I think is unfounded.</p>
<p>Otherwise, the glowing information you write about the possibility of Apple putting more of the latest and the greatest technology into iPhone is fascinating.</p>

    	</div>

		
